{
  "texts": [
    "This survey gives a particular focus on how different federated learning solutions address statistical heterogeneity.The robust model aggregation has recently garnered considerable attention.",
    "Traditionally, client contributions are weighted according to their sample quantity, while recent research has introduced adaptive weighting [9,10], attentive aggregation [11], regularization [12], clustering [13], and Bayesian methods [14].",
    "Many methods generally attempt to derive client characteristics by adjusting the relative weights better.",
    "Aggregation in the federated setting has also addressed fairness [15] in taking underrepresented clients and classes better into account.Statistical heterogeneity, or non-IID data, leads to the difficulties of choosing models and performing hyperparameter tuning, as the data resides at clients, out of the reach of a preliminary analysis.",
    "The edge clients provide the supervision signal for supervised machine learning models."
  ]
}